 
✅ QUESTION 1: Multiple Regression + Diagnostics
(A) Data Structure
data <- read.csv("winequality-red.csv")

# Missing values
sum(is.na(data))

# Variable types
str(data)
 
(B) Baseline Model
model1 <- lm(quality ~ alcohol + volatile.acidity, data=data)
summary(model1)
👉 Interpretation (1 line each):
•	alcohol (+): higher alcohol → better quality
•	volatile acidity (−): higher acidity → worse quality
 
(C) Extended Model
model2 <- lm(quality ~ alcohol + volatile.acidity + residual.sugar + pH, data=data)
summary(model2)
 
(D) Omitted Variable Bias
coef(model1)
coef(model2)
👉 Write:
•	If coefficient changes → OVB exists
•	Direction:
o	If omitted variable positively correlated → upward bias
o	If negatively → downward bias
 
(E) Diagnostics
VIF (Multicollinearity)
install.packages("car")
library(car)
vif(model2)
Breusch-Pagan (Heteroscedasticity)
install.packages("lmtest")
library(lmtest)
bptest(model2)
👉 Remedies:
•	Robust SE → coeftest(model2, vcov = vcovHC(model2))
•	Transform variables (log)
•	Remove correlated variables
 
